g no_action unless research suggests otherwise, and it looks like the evidence isn’t pointing to extra setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No Docker service, optional dependency, or one-time library setup is needed. The artifact is a Maven plugin whose normal reachable surface can be exercised in-process; the reported javac failure is caused by the generated HelpMojo package moving in 3.4.0, not by missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For 3.4.0, use `org.apache.maven.plugins.maven_jar_plugin.HelpMojo` rather than the old `org.apache.maven.plugins.jar.HelpMojo`; invoking the help mojo exercises bundled plugin-help metadata without requiring a Maven runtime or external service.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Exercising `JarMojo`/`TestJarMojo` beyond construction may require Maven-project field injection and careful temporary project setup; the simpler help-goal path avoids that complexity while still covering plugin resource access.\",\n    \"The existing scaffold already adds `maven-plugin-api`; do not add Maven core or plugin-testing harness unless the generated test deliberately performs full Maven mojo lookup/execution.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_070b3d48a2620482016a27adc921c48197960f4ac1a2666453\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2397, "output": 755, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27216, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780985273999, "responseId": "resp_070b3d48a2620482016a27adba8ae8819793df9661ef3aa78f"}}
